# AI/ML Project Configurations

# 1. Track heavy PyTorch model weights using Git Large File Storage (LFS)
# Since you're no longer ignoring them, this prevents GitHub from rejecting large uploads.
*.pt filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.pth filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# 2. Tell GitHub Linguist that this is a Machine Learning (Python) project
# By vendoring the frontend and data folders, GitHub's language bar won't be overwhelmed by JavaScript/HTML.
# It will predominantly show Python as the main language of the repository.
frontend/** linguist-vendored
frontend/package-lock.json linguist-generated
model_training/data/** linguist-generated
model_training/runs/** linguist-generated
model_training/outputs/** linguist-generated
